# Intentionally empty.
#
# Agent Vault is invoked per-process via `agent-vault vault run -- <cmd>`
# (see ~/bin/zshaliases for the claude/codex wrappers). The CLI sets up
# HTTPS_PROXY + CA env scoped to that one child process tree, which is the
# project's recommended pattern.
#
# We deliberately do NOT export HTTPS_PROXY / SSL_CERT_FILE / CURL_CA_BUNDLE
# / etc globally from this file. Doing so was the source of recurring cert
# errors:
#   - tools that don't honor those env vars (libalpm, Go-based binaries
#     using only system roots) were forced through the MITM proxy and
#     failed TLS verification on passthrough hosts (AUR, GitHub, lmstudio.ai)
#   - shells started before any cert-bundle change kept stale env forever
#   - the workaround was a custom "system-CAs + MITM-CA" merged bundle, but
#     the agent-vault proxy itself terminates client TLS with leaves minted
#     by the MITM CA and re-establishes upstream TLS using its own internal
#     trust store, so the merged bundle was solving a self-inflicted problem
